 offers a powerful defense of civility, the versatile human capacity to deflect aggression into sociability and to exercise power over power itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCourtesy. 0aInhibition. 0aSocial ethics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Social.2bisacsh  aabstinence.  acare.  acivility.  agesture.  amanners.  apoliteness.  arestraint.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361084240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610842423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610842.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPHb2020